<subSubSection pageId="221" pageNumber="222" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="221.[151,1437,1167,1504]" pageId="221" pageNumber="222">
8 species are included in this genus from South America. As with other genera of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heer" authorityYear="1839" box="[1066,1212,1167,1192]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="221" pageNumber="222" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Coprophilini">Coprophilini</taxonomicName>
, most of the species are lacking strong internal sclerites in the aedeagi and species-specific female genitalia, therefore are very difficult to separate [György Makranczy, personal communication].
</paragraph>
